subsection.p:
To measure the amount of deformation from the initial length as a fraction, it is customary to introduce a quantity, called the strain or relative deformation, by the following relation:

	\text{Strain} = \dfrac{\text{Deformation}}{\text{Original Length}} =\dfrac{\Delta L}{L_0}  

Clearly, strain is a dimensionless quantity since it is a ratio of two lengths.
